2) Salmonellae with deletion mutations in either trxA or the atp operon offered significant protection against stringent and virulent re-challenge. This was the case regardless of the route of vaccination or re-challenge and provides strong evidence that these mutants have strong potential for further development as live attenuated vaccine strains.

3) Both mutants, but especially trxA, although providing protection equivalent to that induced by SL3261, a prototype vaccine strain, did so with reduced reactogenicity, a major advantage for a potential vaccine strain.</gtr:description><gtr:exploitationPathways>These mutants could form the basis of excellent anti-Salmonella live vaccines, with greatly reduced reactogenicity. They could then also be used as carriers of antigens from other pathogens to make combined vaccines.</gtr:exploitationPathways><gtr:id>1134BEAC-AE79-41FB-A5D2-C315DB569C4E</gtr:id><gtr:outcomeId>r-8450048787.938477779e0dba</gtr:outcomeId><gtr:sectors><gtr:sector>Agriculture, Food and Drink,Healthcare</gtr:sector></gtr:sectors></gtr:keyFindingsOutput><gtr:otherResearchOutputs/><gtr:policyInfluenceOutputs/><gtr:productOutputs/><gtr:researchDatabaseAndModelOutputs/><gtr:researchMaterialOutputs/><gtr:softwareAndTechnicalProductOutputs/><gtr:spinOutOutputs/></gtr:output><gtr:publications><gtr:publication><gtr:id>B6CD26D1-5ACF-40CD-91D5-BF0FA79E40ED</gtr:id><gtr:title>Deletion of tolA in Salmonella Typhimurium generates an attenuated strain with vaccine potential.</gtr:title><gtr:parentPublicationTitle>Microbiology (Reading, England)</gtr:parentPublicationTitle><gtr:authors><gtr:author url="http://gtr.ukri.org:80/person/8f7b6b67c2c4dd1acbb08cdbfbd4caed"><gtr:id>8f7b6b67c2c4dd1acbb08cdbfbd4caed</gtr:id><gtr:otherNames>Paterson GK</gtr:otherNames></gtr:author></gtr:authors><gtr:date>2009-01-01</gtr:date><gtr:issn>1350-0872</gtr:issn><gtr:outcomeId>doi_53d04c04c0c4463f</gtr:outcomeId></gtr:publication><gtr:publication><gtr:id>4A2F4592-4B8C-4D29-BD64-35602C942A27</gtr:id><gtr:title>Salmonella enterica serovar typhimurium trxA mutants are protective against virulent challenge and induce less inflammation than the live-attenuated vaccine strain SL3261.</gtr:title><gtr:parentPublicationTitle>Infection and immunity</gtr:parentPublicationTitle><gtr:authors><gtr:author url="http://gtr.ukri.org:80/person/901d76